column2: WHAT IS THE SEMESTER AVERAGE AND HOW IS IT CALCULATED
column5: The sum of the marks for each subject divided by the number of hours and the sum is#Newline        divided by the total number of hours (all subjects studied during the semester).<break/>#Newline        you can use the calculater in this app to calculate it for you eaisly.

column2: HOW TO CALCULATE THE SEMESTER AVERAGE
column5: The semester average is calculated by summing the marks for each subject and dividing the sum by the total number of hours (all subjects studied during the semester).<break/>#Newline        You can easily calculate it using the calculator in this app.

column2: HOW DOES A STUDENT RECEIVE ACADEMIC WARNINGS
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        Academic warnings are typically issued when a student's academic performance falls below the university's standards. These warnings serve as indicators to address potential issues and improve performance.

column2: WHAT ACTIONS LEAD TO ACADEMIC WARNINGS
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        Academic warnings can result from factors such as consistently low grades#Comma failure to meet attendance requirements#Comma or academic misconduct. It's important to adhere to university policies to avoid receiving warnings.

column2: CAN I AVOID ACADEMIC WARNINGS
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        Yes#Comma academic warnings can be avoided by maintaining consistent attendance#Comma actively participating in classes#Comma seeking academic support when needed#Comma and adhering to the university's code of conduct.

column2: HOW SERIOUS ARE ACADEMIC WARNINGS
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        Academic warnings are a serious indication that a student's performance is not meeting the university's expectations. It is crucial to address the issues leading to the warning promptly.

column2: WHERE CAN I FIND INFORMATION ABOUT ACADEMIC WARNINGS
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        Detailed information about academic warnings#Comma including the university's policies and procedures#Comma can be found in the official student guide. You can access it on the university's website.

column2: WHAT HAPPENS IF I IGNORE ACADEMIC WARNINGS
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        Ignoring academic warnings may lead to more severe consequences#Comma such as academic probation or dismissal. It is highly recommended to take immediate action and seek assistance to improve academic performance.

column2: HOW CAN I ADDRESS ACADEMIC WARNINGS
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        To address academic warnings#Comma schedule a meeting with your academic advisor#Comma create a plan for improvement#Comma and utilize university resources such as tutoring services. Taking proactive steps is essential for success.

column2: ARE ACADEMIC WARNINGS COMMON
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        Academic warnings are not uncommon#Comma and many students receive them as a way to identify areas for improvement. The key is to view them as opportunities to enhance academic performance.

column2: CAN ACADEMIC WARNINGS BE APPEALED
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        In certain circumstances#Comma academic warnings can be appealed. Check the university's policies and procedures for the specific steps and criteria for appealing academic warnings.

column2: HOW DO ACADEMIC WARNINGS AFFECT MY ACADEMIC RECORD
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        Academic warnings are typically part of the student's academic record. While they do not carry a permanent penalty#Comma they serve as a record of past performance. It is crucial to improve to maintain a positive academic standing.

column2: WHAT SHOULD I DO IF I RECEIVE AN ACADEMIC WARNING
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        If you receive an academic warning#Comma schedule a meeting with your academic advisor to discuss the specific issues. Develop a plan for improvement#Comma utilize available resources#Comma and take proactive steps to address the underlying concerns.

Examples include warnings for low grades#Comma attendance#Comma or academic misconduct. Familiarize yourself with the types relevant to your situation.

column2: HOW ARE ACADEMIC WARNINGS COMMUNICATED TO STUDENTS
column5: <srai>What are the academic warnings that a student gets</srai>#Newline        Academic warnings are typically communicated to students through official university channels#Comma such as email or the student portal. It is essential to regularly check your university communications for important updates.

column2: CAN ACADEMIC WARNINGS BE REMOVED FROM MY RECORD

column5: The student may submit a request to postpone their studies by using the prescribed form.#Newline        This request should be submitted before the end of the second week of the semester.#Newline         <button>#Newline            <text>Learn more on page 14</text>#Newline            <url>https://pic.hu.edu.jo/Upload/42000000/%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA%20%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AD%20%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%AC%D8%A9%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%B3%202016%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1%20%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%84%2027-2-2019.pdf</url>#Newline        </button>

column2: WHAT ARE THE CONSEQUENCES OF NOT ADHERING TO THE STUDY POSTPONEMENT DEADLINES
column5: Failure to adhere to the study postponement deadlines may result in academic penalties.#Newline        It is crucial to follow the specified procedures and timelines#Comma as outlined in the instructions for granting a bachelor’s degree and the student guide electronically.#Newline        <button>#Newline            <text>Learn more on page 14</text>#Newline            <url>https://pic.hu.edu.jo/Upload/42000000/%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA%20%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AD%20%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%AC%D8%A9%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%B3%202016%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1%20%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%84%2027-2-2019.pdf</url>#Newline        </button>

column2: IS THERE A MAXIMUM PERIOD FOR STUDY POSTPONEMENT
column5: Yes#Comma there is a maximum period for study postponement#Comma and it should not exceed five compulsory semesters#Comma whether intermittent or continuous.#Newline        It is important to adhere to this limit and refer to the guidelines in the instructions for granting a bachelor’s degree and the student guide electronically.#Newline      <button>#Newline            <text>Learn more on page 14</text>#Newline            <url>https://pic.hu.edu.jo/Upload/42000000/%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA%20%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AD%20%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%AC%D8%A9%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%B3%202016%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1%20%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%84%2027-2-2019.pdf</url>#Newline        </button>

column2: HOW CAN I CHECK THE STATUS OF MY STUDY POSTPONEMENT REQUEST
column5: You can check the status of your study postponement request through the university portal or by contacting the relevant department.#Newline        Ensure to follow up on your request and meet any additional requirements#Comma if necessary.

column2: WHAT ARE THE COMMON REASONS FOR STUDY POSTPONEMENT
column5: Study postponement is commonly allowed for reasons such as medical conditions#Comma family emergencies#Comma or other compelling circumstances.#Newline        Make sure to provide supporting documentation when submitting your request.

column2: WHAT HAPPENS IF MY STUDY POSTPONEMENT REQUEST IS DENIED
column5: If your study postponement request is denied#Comma you should consult with the Dean of Student Affairs or the relevant department for further guidance.#Newline        They can provide insights into the denial reasons and discuss potential alternatives.

column2: CAN I APPEAL A DENIED STUDY POSTPONEMENT REQUEST
column5: Yes#Comma you can appeal a denied study postponement request. Follow the university's appeal process and provide any additional information that supports your case.

column2: WHAT IS THE PROCESS FOR WITHDRAWING A STUDY POSTPONEMENT REQUEST
column5: If you wish to withdraw your study postponement request#Comma contact the relevant department or the Dean of Student Affairs as soon as possible.#Newline        Provide a clear explanation for your decision and follow any required procedures.

column2: IS THERE A FEE ASSOCIATED WITH STUDY POSTPONEMENT
column5: There may be specific fees associated with study postponement. Check the university's fee structure or contact the relevant department for accurate information.#Newline        Be aware of any financial implications before submitting your request.

column2: ARE THERE ALTERNATIVES TO STUDY POSTPONEMENT
column5: In some cases#Comma alternatives to study postponement may include course withdrawals#Comma taking a reduced course load#Comma or exploring flexible scheduling options.#Newline        Discuss your situation with academic advisors to explore the best alternatives for your circumstances.

column2: CAN INTERNATIONAL STUDENTS APPLY FOR STUDY POSTPONEMENT
column5: Yes#Comma international students can apply for study postponement. However#Comma they should consider potential visa implications and communicate with the international student office for guidance.

column2: WHAT ARE THE STEPS TO APPLY FOR STUDY POSTPONEMENT
column5: The steps to apply for study postponement include completing the prescribed form#Comma providing necessary documentation#Comma and submitting the request before the specified deadline.#Newline        Follow the guidelines outlined in the university's instructions for granting a bachelor’s degree and the student guide electronically.#Newline        <button>#Newline            <text>Learn more on page 14</text>#Newline            <url>https://pic.hu.edu.jo/Upload/42000000/%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA%20%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AD%20%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%AC%D8%A9%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%B3%202016%D8%A2%D8%AE%D8%B1%20%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%84%2027-2-2019.pdf</url>#Newline        </button>

column2: HOW MANY SEMESTERS CAN I POSTPONE AND WHAT IS THE LEGAL PERIOD FOR ME TO STAY AT THE UNIVERSITY

column2: WHAT ARE THE CONDITIONS FOR TRANSFERRING TO THE UNIVERSITY FROM ANOTHER JORDANIAN UNIVERSITY
column5:
To transfer to the university from another official Jordanian university#Comma the following conditions must be met:#Newline
    #Newline
  1. A seat must be available for the student in the specialty he wishes to transfer to.
    2. #Newline
  2. The student must have successfully studied no less than (33) credit hours at his current university#Comma which are included in the calculation of his cumulative grades. These grades are not included in calculating his cumulative average at the university.
    3. #Newline
  3. The student's GPA in high school must be acceptable either in the year he obtained high school or the year he applied for the transfer. A very good cumulative average is required. In this case#Comma the student must move to the same subjects he studied at his current university#Comma no less than the major in which he is accepted at the university for regular study.
    4. #Newline
  4. The student must not have been expelled from his current university.
    5. #Newline
  5. The Dean of the College may consider the possibility of the student transferring to a major close to his current major if it is not available at the university.
    6. #Newline
#Newline
